<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="345" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="20.[112,647,715,1083]" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">
DISTRIBUTION. — In 
<collectingCountry box="[327,379,715,739]" name="Togo" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">Togo</collectingCountry>
, this species has been mentioned from “Klien Popo”, now Aneho, by Sternfeld (1908a-b, 1909) and 
<bibRefCitation author="LOVERIDGE A." box="[334,563,768,792]" pageId="20" pageNumber="345" pagination="121 - 247" refId="ref27999" refString="LOVERIDGE A. 1944. - Further revisions of African snake genera. Bulletin of the the Museum of Comparative Zoology 95: 121 - 247." type="journal article" year="1944">Loveridge (1944: 173)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="WERNER F." pageId="20" pageNumber="345" pagination="191 - 230" refId="ref29615" refString="WERNER F. 1898. - Uber Reptilien und Batrachier aus Togoland, Kamerun undTunis dem Kgl. Museum fur Naturkunde in Berlin. Verhandlungen der kaiserlichkoniglichen Zoologisch-botanischen Gesellschaft inWien 58: 191 - 230, 1 plate." type="book chapter" year="1898">Werner (1898</bibRefCitation>
; as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1923" box="[213,393,795,819]" genus="Miodon" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="20" pageNumber="345" rank="species" species="gabonensis">
<emphasis box="[213,393,795,819]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">Miodon gabonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) mentioned from 
<collectingCountry box="[578,628,795,819]" name="Togo" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">Togo</collectingCountry>
a specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dumeril, 1858)" baseAuthorityName="Dumeril" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[239,599,821,845]" class="Reptilia" family="Lamprophiidae" genus="Polemon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="345" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gabonensis">
<emphasis box="[239,423,821,845]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">Polemon gabonensis</emphasis>
(Duméril, 1858)
</taxonomicName>
. The current distribution of this species extends from eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[112,184,874,898]" name="Nigeria" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[221,288,874,898]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">Congo</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="CHIPPAUX J. - P." box="[302,464,874,898]" pageId="20" pageNumber="345" refId="ref26729" refString="CHIPPAUX J. - P. 2006. - Les serpents d'Afrique Occidentale et Centrale. Collection Faune et Flore tropicales, Paris, IRD Editions 35: 311 p." type="book" year="2006">Chippaux 2006</bibRefCitation>
). It is hence likely that Werner’s specimen should be referred to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Jan" baseAuthorityYear="1858" class="Reptilia" family="Lamprophiidae" genus="Polemon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="345" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="neuwiedi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">Polemon neuwiedi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although another taxon of the same genus cannot be ruled out. This confusion may also apply to the Togolese record of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Peters, 1881) in Werner (1898)" authorityName="in Werner" authorityYear="1898" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1881" class="Reptilia" family="Lamprophiidae" genus="Polemon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="345" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="collaris">
<emphasis box="[343,498,980,1004]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">Polemon collaris</emphasis>
(Peters, 1881) in 
<bibRefCitation author="WERNER F." box="[141,291,1007,1031]" pageId="20" pageNumber="345" pagination="191 - 230" refId="ref29615" refString="WERNER F. 1898. - Uber Reptilien und Batrachier aus Togoland, Kamerun undTunis dem Kgl. Museum fur Naturkunde in Berlin. Verhandlungen der kaiserlichkoniglichen Zoologisch-botanischen Gesellschaft inWien 58: 191 - 230, 1 plate." type="book chapter" year="1898">Werner (1898)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. This author was merely followed by 
<bibRefCitation author="STERNFELD L." box="[113,279,1033,1057]" pageId="20" pageNumber="345" pagination="207 - 236" refId="ref29004" refString="STERNFELD L. 1908 b. - Die Schlangenfauna Togos. Mittheilungen Zoologischen Museum in Berlin 4: 207 - 236." type="journal article" year="1908">Sternfeld (1908b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="STERNFELD L." box="[289,341,1033,1057]" pageId="20" pageNumber="345" refId="ref29026" refString="STERNFELD L. 1909. - Die Schlangen Togos, in Die Fauna der deutschen Kolonien 1 (1): iv + 29 p., map." type="book" year="1909">1909</bibRefCitation>
) but 
<bibRefCitation author="LOVERIDGE A." box="[392,559,1033,1057]" pageId="20" pageNumber="345" pagination="121 - 247" refId="ref27999" refString="LOVERIDGE A. 1944. - Further revisions of African snake genera. Bulletin of the the Museum of Comparative Zoology 95: 121 - 247." type="journal article" year="1944">Loveridge (1944)</bibRefCitation>
doubted about the occurrence of this latter species in 
<collectingCountry box="[547,600,1059,1083]" name="Togo" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">Togo</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[188,571,1134,1193]" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">
