<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="345" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="20.[112,647,1464,1699]" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">
DISTRIBUTION. — This species inhabits 
<collectingCountry box="[487,547,1464,1488]" name="Sudan" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">Sudan</collectingCountry>
savannahs (ER I). Previously it had been described from 
<collectingCountry box="[594,645,1490,1514]" name="Togo" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">Togo</collectingCountry>
(Mango) by 
<bibRefCitation author="STERNFELD L." box="[244,424,1516,1540]" pageId="20" pageNumber="345" pagination="207 - 236" refId="ref29004" refString="STERNFELD L. 1908 b. - Die Schlangenfauna Togos. Mittheilungen Zoologischen Museum in Berlin 4: 207 - 236." type="journal article" year="1908">Sternfeld (1908b)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authority="Sternfeld, 1908" authorityName="Sternfeld" authorityYear="1908" class="Reptilia" family="Lamprophiidae" genus="Prosymna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="345" phylum="Chordata" rank="variety" species="meleagris" variety="collaris">
<emphasis box="[457,647,1516,1540]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">Prosymna meleagris</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[152,217,1543,1567]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">collaris</emphasis>
Sternfeld, 1908
</taxonomicName>
. This form was subsequently synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Reinhardt, 1843)" baseAuthorityName="Reinhardt" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[292,646,1569,1593]" class="Reptilia" family="Lamprophiidae" genus="Prosymna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="345" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meleagris">
<emphasis box="[292,469,1569,1593]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">Prosymna meleagris</emphasis>
(Reinhardt, 1843)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="LOVERIDGE A." box="[140,308,1596,1620]" pageId="20" pageNumber="345" pagination="1 - 198" refId="ref28026" refString="LOVERIDGE A. 1958. - Revision of five snake genera. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology 119 (1): 1 - 198." type="journal article" year="1958">Loveridge (1958)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="TRAPE J. - F. &amp; MANE Y." box="[314,536,1596,1620]" pageId="20" pageNumber="345" refId="ref29189" refString="TRAPE J. - F. &amp; MANE Y. 2006 b. - Guide des serpents d'Afrique occidentale (savane et desert). IRD Editions, Paris, 226 p." type="book" year="2006">Trape &amp; Mané (2006b)</bibRefCitation>
revalidated 
<taxonomicName authority="Mocquard, 1906" authorityName="Mocquard" authorityYear="1906" box="[112,444,1622,1646]" class="Reptilia" family="Lamprophiidae" genus="Prosymna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="345" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gregerti">
<emphasis box="[112,275,1623,1646]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">Prosymna gregerti</emphasis>
Mocquard, 1906
</taxonomicName>
as a valid taxon. This species was mentioned fom northern 
<collectingCountry box="[487,538,1649,1673]" name="Togo" pageId="20" pageNumber="345">Togo</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="VILLIERS A." pageId="20" pageNumber="345" pagination="17 - 46" refId="ref29471" refString="VILLIERS A. 1951. - Mission A. Villiers au Togo et au Dahomey (1950) II. - Ophidiens. Etudes dahomeennes, Centre IFAN 5: 17 - 46." type="journal article" year="1951">Villiers (1951)</bibRefCitation>
and Villiers &amp; Condamin (2005).
</paragraph>
